<EXTRAINFO>Bankruptcy for U.S. automaker GM becomes almost certain after bondholder offers fail</EXTRAINFO>
<TEXT><s id="0">Bankruptcy for U.S. automaker GM becomes almost certain after bondholder offers fail</s><s id="1">May 28 , 2009</s><s id="2">The United States automobile manufacturing firm General Motors announced on Wednesday that most of its bondholders did not exchange GM 's US$ 27 billion debt for a ten percent share in the company 's stock .</s><s id="3">The automaker , in financial straits , has a June 1 deadline to finish a government restructuring plan that includes plant closures and other debt reduction measures .</s><s id="4">U.S. President Barack Obama 's administration said it would not give more financial aid to the firm unless 90 % of GM 's bondholders would agree on compromises that would significantly reduce the firm 's costs .</s><s id="5">`` The principal amount of notes tendered was substantially less than the amount required by GM to satisfy the debt reduction requirement , '' GM said in a statement .</s><s id="6">`` They said no .</s><s id="7">That 's it .</s><s id="8">They tried .</s><s id="9">That 's why they 're going to have to file for bankruptcy , '' said a university professor from the University of Michigan who specializes in bankruptcy .</s></TEXT>
